Navigate to other release versions of Doxee Platform Process Designer

[6.6](https://docs.doxee.com/docs/en/process-designer-6-6)

[6.7](https://docs.doxee.com/docs/en/process-designer-6-7)

Download the installer on your system and start it.

## Startup
The *Installation Wizard* starts and unpacks several files that are needed for the installation.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

## Language Selection
First, the installation program asks in which language the installation should be done.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

You can choose between English and German. The language of the first two dialogs depends on the language setting of the operating system.

## User Account Control
Because the installation process needs administrator privileges, Windows is likely (depending on its configuration) to notify you of this fact.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

Again, the language of this dialog depends on the language setting of the operating system. Click "Yes" to contiue the installation.

## Welcome
![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

## Select Components
![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

Pick the components that you wish to install, and the installation base directory. For more information on the components, click the question mark icon next to the components.

Whenever any part of the documentation mentions the *installation directory*, it refers to the directory that you choose in this dialog.

## Select Start Menu Folder
![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

When several users of this computer use the *Infinica Design Tools* or when the installation is done by a different user, the option *Create shortcuts for all users* should be selected.

## Select File Associations
![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

Depending on the installed components you selected before, not all of the file types in the screenshot may be offered, or the screen may be skipped altogether.

## Settings Location
![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

Select where the *Design Tools* shall store their settings. The segment "@user.home" refers to the home directory of the user who runs the application, not the user who installs it. This results in every user having his or her own settings. If you want to use common settings for all users, pick a physical directory on your disk without this segment.

## Program Language
![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

You can select a language for the program which is different from the language for the installation process.

## Java Runtime Environment (JRE)
![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

Select the JRE the application should use. You can use the JRE that is bundled with the product, the standard system JRE, or a specific JRE from your system.

Note that the *Infinica* applications have been tested with the bundled JRE. Use a different JRE at your own risk!

## Installing
![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

The installation program unpacks and copies the files to the selected directory.

## Finish
![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

When the installation is finished, you can read the "Whats New" document and you can activate your license (unless you installed *Resource Explorer* only, which does not require a license).

It is recommended to activate the license directly from the Setup, as Administrator. This way, the license is activated for all users. Otherwise, every user starting one the the Design Tools for the first time on this computer will be prompted for a license file.

Click *Finish*.
